# Inventory & Economy Local Runtime Context

You are working in a local inventory or economy runtime/test hotspot.

Start from touched code/tests in these roots first. Do NOT auto-load `docs/design/core-architecture.md` for local inventory transfer, storage, checkout, or shop-flow cleanup.

Read `docs/design/README.md` only to decide whether a domain doc is needed. Load docs only as needed:

1. `docs/design/inventory-and-economy.md` when local semantics are unclear
2. `docs/design/save-contract-quick-reference.md` and `docs/design/save-and-progression.md` only if the touched seam changes persisted ownership, location, or restore behavior
3. `docs/design/extensible-development-contracts.md` only for cross-domain interaction or UI bridge changes
4. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` only if the change crosses events, save, persistence, or another domain, or if local intent is unclear
5. `.agent/skills/refactoring-and-test-hygiene/SKILL.md` for local runtime refactor/test cleanup

If the task becomes inventory/economy data-content, prefab authoring, or cross-domain integration work, switch to `.cursor/rules/inventory-economy-context.mdc`.
